## Major Varieties

**Black Molly:** Near-uniform jet-black colouration; the most iconic. Melanophore-dominant selection from *P. sphenops*. Males develop subtle iridescence.

**Dalmatian Molly:** White base with irregular black spots — resembling a Dalmatian dog. Attractive and popular beginner choice.

**Dalmatian Lyretail:** Dalmatian pattern combined with elongated lyre-shaped caudal fin rays in both sexes.

**Balloon Molly:** Aberrant body shape with shortened, rounded body and curved spine. The balloon body shape is the result of a spinal deformity that has been selectively maintained in the hobby. Note: these fish have reduced swimming efficiency and are more susceptible to internal organ compression issues. Welfare concerns are valid.

**Sailfin Molly:** *P. latipinna* — Larger body with spectacular extended dorsal fin in mature males. The dorsal fin is raised and spread during courtship displays. Requires larger tanks than short-fin varieties.

**Gold Dust Molly:** Yellow-gold base colour with black spots; iridescent "gold dust" shimmer.

**Platinum Molly:** Metallic white/silver colouration.

**Creamsicle Lyretail:** Orange and white with lyretail fin form.

