## Feeding

Mollies are omnivores with a strong herbivorous component — more plant-based than most hobby fish.

**Staple foods:**
- High-quality omnivore/community pellets or flakes
- Spirulina flakes or wafers — Plant-based nutrition well-suited to their herbivorous tendencies
- Algae wafers (shared with Plecos and Corydoras)
- Blanched vegetables: zucchini, spinach, peas (shelled)

**Protein supplementation (2–3x per week):**
- Frozen bloodworm
- Frozen brine shrimp
- Daphnia (live preferred for enrichment)

**Live foods for breeding conditioning:**
- **Baby Brine Shrimp** — Excellent pre-breeding conditioning. **[Available at Blackwater Aquatics](https://blackwateraquatics.ca/collections/live-foods).**
- **Daphnia** — Fibre-rich; good for digestive health. **[Available at Blackwater Aquatics](https://blackwateraquatics.ca/collections/live-foods).**

**Algae grazing:** Mollies actively graze algae from tank surfaces. This is beneficial — a light algae coating on glass provides supplemental nutrition and natural grazing behaviour. Don't scrape all glass algae if keeping Mollies.

