## Compatible Tankmates

Mollies are generally peaceful community fish. Avoid fin-nipping species around Sailfin Mollies (the large dorsal fin is an irresistible target for barbs and tiger barbs).

**Compatible:**
- **[Platy Fish](/species/platy-fish)** — Fellow livebearer; same water parameters
- **[Guppy](/species/guppy)** — Livebearer community; note Guppies prefer softer water than ideal for Mollies
- **[Corydoras](/species/corydoras)** — Different water hardness preference (Corydoras prefer softer); monitor
- Swordtails — Similar habitat and livebearer biology
- **[Bristlenose Pleco](/species/bristlenose-pleco)** — Algae grazing complement

**Avoid:**
- Soft-water species (Neon Tetras, Discus, Blackwater fish) — Water chemistry conflict
- Tiger Barbs — Fin nipping on Sailfins
- Aggressive cichlids

